description: A first person narrative of the exploits of a gay serial killer in deeply disturbing, controversial drama about violence, sexuality, and the imagination. Dennis, the main character, whose lead we follow on this path between what i...

name: Friday the 13th Part VII: The New Blood
description: Jason Voorhees is accidentally freed from his watery prison by a telekinetic teenager. Now, only she can stop him.

name: Friday the 13th Part VIII: Jason Takes Manhattan
description: Jason Voorhees is accidentally awakened from his watery grave, and he ends up stalking a ship full of graduating high school students headed to Manhattan, NY.

name: Halloween
description: Fifteen years after murdering his sister on Halloween night 1963, Michael Myers escapes from a mental hospital and returns to the small town of Haddonfield, Illinois to kill again.

name: Halloween II
description: While Dr. Loomis hunts for Michael Myers, a traumatized Laurie is rushed to Haddonfield Memorial Hospital, and The Shape is not far behind her.

name: Halloween III: Season of the Witch
description: Kids all over America want Silver Shamrock masks for Halloween. Doctor Daniel Challis seeks to uncover a plot by Silver Shamrock owner Conal Cochran.

name: Halloween 4: The Return of Michael Myers
description: Ten years after his original massacre, the invalid Michael Myers awakens on Halloween Eve and returns to Haddonfield to kill his seven-year-old niece. Can Dr. Loomis stop him?

name: Halloween 5: The Revenge of Michael Myers
description: One year after the events of Halloween 4: The Return of Michael Myers (1988), the Shape returns to Haddonfield once again in an attempt to kill his now-mute niece.

name: Prom Night
description: At a high school senior prom, a masked killer stalks four teenagers who were responsible for the accidental death of a classmate six years previously.

name: Prom Night IV: Deliver Us From Evil
description: Four students ditch their high school prom for a party at a summer home, unaware that a psychotic priest is on the loose, determined to punish sinners.

name: Child's Play
description: A single mother gives her son a much sought-after doll for his birthday, only to discover that it is possessed by the soul of a serial killer.

name: Child's Play 2
description: While Andy's mother is admitted to a psychiatric hospital, the young boy is placed in foster care, and Chucky, determined to claim Andy's soul, is not far behind.

name: Child's Play 3
description: Chucky returns for revenge against Andy, the young boy who defeated him, and now a teenager living in a military academy.

name: Poltergeist
description: A family's home is haunted by a host of demonic ghosts.

name: Poltergeist II: The Other Side
description: The Freeling family have a new house, but their troubles with supernatural forces don't seem to be over.

name: Poltergeist III
description: Carol Anne is staying with her aunt in a high-rise building, where the supernatural forces haunting her make their return.

name: Exorcist, The
description: When a teenage girl is possessed by a mysterious entity, her mother seeks the help of two priests to save her daughter.

name: Exorcist II: The Heretic
description: A teenage girl once possessed by a demon finds that it still lurks within her. Meanwhile, a priest investigates the death of the girl's exorcist.

name: Exorcist III, The
description: A police lieutenant uncovers more than he bargained for as his investigation of a series of murders, which have all the hallmarks of the deceased Gemini serial killer, leads him to question the patients of a psychiatric ward.

name: Lethal Weapon
description: Two newly paired cops who are complete opposites must put aside their differences in order to catch a gang of drug smugglers.

name: Lethal Weapon 2
description: Riggs and Murtaugh are on the trail of South African diplomats who are using their immunity to engage in criminal activities.

name: Lethal Weapon 3
description: Martin Riggs and Roger Murtaugh pursue a former LAPD officer who uses his knowledge of police procedure and policies to steal and sell confiscated guns and ammunition to local street gangs.

name: Gremlins
description: A young man inadvertently breaks three important rules concerning his new pet and unleashes a horde of malevolently mischievous monsters on a small town.

name: Gremlins 2: The New Batch
description: The Gremlins are back, and this time, they've taken control of a New York City media mogul's high-tech skyscraper.

name: Goonies, The
description: A group of young misfits called The Goonies discover an ancient map and set out on an adventure to find a legendary pirate's long-lost treasure.

name: Mask of Zorro, The
description: A young thief seeking revenge for his brother's death is trained by the once-great, aging Zorro, who is pursuing his own vengeance.

name: Polish Wedding
description: The film centers on a big Polish family. Jadzia is the mother and the ruler of the Pzoniak family (she has five children). Though she's happily married to Bolek, she is also having a long-time affair with Roman. Her young daughter...

name: This World, Then the Fireworks
description: In 1950s, two incestuous lovers, a depraved suave journalist and his equally depraved prostitute sister, plan to get rich through seduction and murder. Things complicate when their feeble-minded mother begins to suspect something.

name: Soylent Green
description: A nightmarish futuristic fantasy about the controlling power of big corporations and an innocent cop who stumbles on the truth.

name: Metropolis
description: In a futuristic city sharply divided between the working class and the city planners, the son of the city's mastermind falls in love with a working-class prophet who predicts the coming of a savior to mediate their differences.

name: Back to the Future Part II
description: After visiting 2015, Marty McFly must repeat his visit to 1955 to prevent disastrous changes to 1985...without interfering with his first trip.

name: Back to the Future Part III
description: Stranded in 1955, Marty McFly learns about the death of Doc Brown in 1885 and must travel back in time to save him. With no fuel readily available for the DeLorean, the two must figure how to escape the Old West before Emmett is m...

name: Poseidon Adventure, The
description: Nine people explore a cruise ship at sea in a manner that turns their whole lives upside down.

name: Freaky Friday
description: A mother and daughter find their personalities switched and have to live each other's lives on one strange Friday.

name: Absent-Minded Professor, The
description: A college professor invents an anti-gravity substance which a corrupt businessman wants for himself.

name: Apple Dumpling Gang Rides Again, The
description: The adventures of two idiotic outlaw wannabees, Amos and Theodore.

name: Babes in Toyland
description: Mary Contrary is set to marry Tom Piper when he is kidnapped by Roderigo and Gonzorgo, two goons working for the evil Barnaby who wants to marry Mary for her inheritance.

name: Bambi
description: The story of a young deer growing up in the forest.

name: Seven Samurai
description: Farmers from a village exploited by bandits hire a veteran samurai for protection, who gathers six other samurai to join him.

name: Dangerous Liaisons
description: A scheming widow and her manipulative ex-lover make a bet regarding the corruption of a recently married woman.

name: Dune
description: A Duke's son leads desert warriors against the galactic emperor and his father's evil nemesis to free their desert world from the emperor's rule.

name: Last Temptation of Christ, The
description: The life of Jesus Christ, his journey through life as he faces the struggles all humans do, and his final temptation on the cross.

name: Godfather: Part III, The
description: Follows Michael Corleone, now in his 60s, as he seeks to free his family from crime and find a suitable successor to his empire.

name: Rapture, The
description: A telephone operator living an empty, amoral life finds God and loses him again.

name: Lolita
description: An English professor falls for a minor, and has to face the consequences of his actions.

name: Disturbing Behavior
description: The new kid in Cradle Bay, Washington stumbles across something sinister about the town's method of transforming its unruly teens into upstanding citizens.

name: Jane Austen's Mafia!
description: Takeoff on the Godfather with the son of a mafia king taking over for his dying father

name: Saving Private Ryan
description: Following the Normandy Landings, a group of U.S. soldiers go behind enemy lines to retrieve a paratrooper whose brothers have been killed in action.

name: Barefoot Executive, The
description: A mailroom clerk and a chimp team up to pick hit TV shows.

name: Black Cauldron, The
description: A young boy and a group of misfit friends embark on a quest to find a dark magic item of ultimate power before a diabolical tyrant can.

name: Black Hole, The
description: A research vessel finds a missing ship, commanded by a mysterious scientist, on the edge of a black hole.

name: Blackbeard's Ghost
description: An unassuming track coach accidentally invokes the spirit of a notorious pirate long believed dead, and who must now team up to lay the pirate to rest, and save a local hotel from a mobster.

name: Blank Check
description: After a bike accident, a young boy inadvertently gains possession of a check for $1 million and proceeds to spend it, unaware that the gangsters it belongs to are in pursuit.

name: Candleshoe
description: Welcome to Candleshoe, a stately English manor where a swashbuckling pirate hid a fortune in Spanish doubloons centuries ago. And that's what young orphan Casey and a sly con man are determined to find.

name: Cat from Outer Space, The
description: Three scientists help an Alien feline, stranded on Earth, to repair its damaged spacecraft in order to return home but their efforts are hampered by inept army officials and foreign spies.

name: Computer Wore Tennis Shoes, The
description: At Medfield College, an accident with a donated computer gives Dexter Riley the ability to remember any knowledge learned instantly and perfectly.

name: Condorman
description: Cartoonist Woody becomes the superhero he draws. Using his gadgets he helps a Soviet spy defect to the West.

name: D2: The Mighty Ducks
description: Can Gordon's team win the Junior Goodwill Games in California in spite of all the set-backs?

name: Darby O'Gill and the Little People
description: A wily old codger matches wits with the King of the Leprechauns and helps play matchmaker for his daughter and the strapping lad who has replaced him as caretaker.

name: Devil and Max Devlin, The
description: Max, a dead corrupt businessman, makes a Faustian pact with Satan's henchman to drive three people to Hell in exchange for longer life. Soon Max realizes that there still may be good in him.

name: Flight of the Navigator
description: In 1978, a boy travels eight years into the future and has an adventure with an intelligent, wisecracking alien ship.

name: Great Mouse Detective, The
description: Basil, the rodent Sherlock Holmes, investigates the kidnapping of a toy maker and uncovers its link to his archenemy, Professor Ratigan.

name: Herbie Goes Bananas
description: The adorable little VW helps its owners break up a counterfeiting ring in Mexico.

name: Herbie Goes to Monte Carlo
description: Herbie, the Volkswagen Beetle with a mind of its own, is racing in the Monte Carlo Rally. Unbeknownst to Herbie's driver, thieves have hidden a cache of stolen diamonds in Herbie's gas tank, and are now trying to get them back.

name: Hocus Pocus
description: A teenage boy named Max and his little sister move to Salem, where he struggles to fit in before awakening a trio of diabolical witches that were executed in the 17th century.

name: Honey, I Blew Up the Kid
description: The Szalinski family is back, this time hilarious disaster strikes when an experiment causes their new toddler son to grow many stories tall.

name: Honey, I Shrunk the Kids
description: The scientist father of a teenage girl and boy accidentally shrinks his and two other neighborhood teens to the size of insects. Now the teens must fight diminutive dangers as the father searches for them.

name: Hot Lead and Cold Feet
description: This saga of the old west involves twin brothers who compete for possession of a rickety cow town founded by their father while a crooked Mayor tries to put an end to the competitors so he can inherit the town himself.

name: In Search of the Castaways
description: In 19th century England, young Mary Grant and her brother, Robert, embark on a dangerous quest to find their missing father, a sea captain who vanished somewhere along the Chilean coast.

name: Incredible Journey, The
description: The story of three pets, a cat and two dogs, who lose their owners when they are all on vacation. Can they find their way home?

name: Negotiator, The
description: In a desperate attempt to prove his innocence, a skilled police negotiator accused of corruption and murder takes hostages in a government office to gain the time he needs to find the truth.

name: Parent Trap, The
description: Identical twins Annie and Hallie, separated at birth and each raised by one of their biological parents, discover each other for the first time at summer camp and make a plan to bring their wayward parents back together.

name: BASEketball
description: Two childhood friends are pro athletes of a national sport called BASEketball, a hybrid of baseball and basketball, and must deal with a greedy businessman scheming against their team.

name: Roger & Me
description: After General Motors closes its factory in Flint, Michigan, eliminating 35,000 jobs, filmmaker Michael Moore undertakes a quixotic quest to interview General Motors' chairman, Roger B. Smith.

name: Purple Rose of Cairo, The
description: In 1935 New Jersey, a movie character walks off the screen and into the real world.

name: Out of the Past
description: A private eye escapes his past to run a gas station in a small town, but his past catches up with him. Now he must return to the big city world of danger, corruption, double crosses, and duplicitous dames.

name: Doctor Zhivago
description: The life of a Russian physician and poet who, although married to another, falls in love with a political activist's wife and experiences hardship during World War I and then the October Revolution.

name: Fanny and Alexander
description: Two young Swedish children in the 1900s experience the many comedies and tragedies of their lively and affectionate theatrical family, the Ekdahls.

name: Trip to Bountiful, The
description: In 1940s Texas, an elderly woman is determined to visit her childhood home one last time.

name: Tender Mercies
description: A broken-down, middle-aged country singer gets a new wife, reaches out to his long-lost daughter, and tries to put his troubled life back together.

name: And the Band Played On
description: The story of the discovery of the AIDS epidemic, and the political infighting of the scientific community hampering the early fight with it.

name: 'burbs, The
description: An overstressed suburbanite and his neighbors are convinced that the new family on the block is part of a murderous Satanic cult.

name: Fandango
description: Five college buddies from the University of Texas circa 1971 embark on a final road trip odyssey across the Mexican border before facing up to uncertain futures, in Vietnam and otherwise.

name: Night Porter, The
description: A concentration camp survivor rekindles her sadomasochistic relationship with her lover, a former SS officer - now working as a night porter at a Vienna hotel - but his former Nazi associates begin stalking them.

name: Mephisto
description: In early-1930s Germany, a passionate stage actor finds himself before a dilemma: renounce his apolitical stance and comply with the Reich's doctrine, or face oblivion. But, Faustian bargains never end well. What is the price of su...

name: Blue Velvet
description: The discovery of a severed human ear found in a field leads a young man on an investigation related to a beautiful, mysterious nightclub singer and a group of psychopathic criminals who have kidnapped her child.

name: Journey of Natty Gann, The
description: In the 1930s, a tomboy runs away from her guardian to join her single father who is 2,000 miles away, where he has found work.

name: Jungle Book, The
description: Bagheera the Panther and Baloo the Bear have a difficult time trying to convince a boy to leave the jungle for human civilization.

name: Lady and the Tramp
description: The romantic tale of a sheltered uptown Cocker Spaniel dog and a streetwise downtown Mutt.

name: Little Mermaid, The
description: A mermaid princess makes a Faustian bargain in an attempt to become human and win a prince's love.

name: Mighty Ducks, The
description: A self-centered Minnesota lawyer is sentenced to community service coaching a rag tag youth hockey team.

name: Muppet Christmas Carol, The
description: The Muppets present their own touching rendition of Charles Dickens' classic tale.

name: Newsies
description: A musical based on the New York City newsboy strike of 1899. When young newspaper sellers are exploited beyond reason by their bosses they set out to enact change and are met by the ruthlessness of big business.

name: 101 Dalmatians
description: When a litter of Dalmatian puppies are abducted by the minions of Cruella De Vil, the owners must find them before she uses them for a diabolical fashion statement.

name: Peter Pan
description: Wendy and her brothers are whisked away to the magical world of Neverland with the hero of their stories, Peter Pan.

name: Popeye
description: The adventures of the famous sailor man and his friends in the seaside town of Sweethaven.

name: Rescuers Down Under, The
description: R.A.S. agents Miss Bianca and Bernard race to Australia to save a little boy and a rare golden eagle from a murderous poacher.

name: Rescuers, The
description: Two mice of the Rescue Aid Society search for a little girl kidnapped by unscrupulous treasure hunters.

name: Return from Witch Mountain
description: Tia and Tony visit Los Angeles, but he's quickly kidnapped by an evil scientist, leaving her to desperately search for him.

name: Return of Jafar, The
description: Jafar comes for revenge on Aladdin, using a foolish thief and Iago's treachery to find a way back into power.

name: Return to Oz
description: Dorothy, saved from a psychiatric experiment by a mysterious girl, is somehow called back to Oz when a vain witch and the Nome King destroy everything that makes the magical land beautiful.

name: Rocketeer, The
description: A young pilot stumbles onto a prototype jetpack that allows him to become a high-flying masked hero.

name: Shaggy D.A., The
description: A lawyer makes an interesting discovery that could affect his chances of getting elected to office.

name: Sleeping Beauty
description: After being snubbed by the royal family, a malevolent fairy places a curse on a princess which only a prince can break, along with the help of three good fairies.

name: Something Wicked This Way Comes
description: In a small American town, a diabolical circus and its demonic proprietor prey on the townsfolk.

name: Son of Flubber
description: When Professor Brainard experiments further on Flubber derivatives, he gets in trouble and only his students can help.

name: Song of the South
description: The kindly story-teller Uncle Remus tells a young boy stories about trickster Br'er Rabbit, who outwits Br'er Fox and slow-witted Br'er Bear.

name: Splash
description: A young man is reunited with a mermaid who saved him from drowning as a boy. He falls in love with her, not knowing who or what she is.

name: Steamboat Willie
description: Mickey Mouse is a mischievous deckhand on a riverboat that is under the command of the tyrannical Captain Pete.

name: Tall Tale
description: A young boy's imagination summons cowboy legend Pecos Bill, who helps him save the family farm from a greedy land-grabber. With the help of a lumberjack and a railroad worker, they all embark on a surprise-filled adventure.

name: Tex
description: After their mother dies and their father leaves them, teenage brothers Tex and Mason McCormick struggle to make it on their own.

name: Tron
description: A computer hacker is abducted into the digital world and forced to participate in gladiatorial games where his only chance of escape is with the help of a heroic security program.

name: Swing Kids
description: A group of teens adores forbidden music in Nazi Germany just before the outbreak of World War II.

name: Halloween H20: 20 Years Later
description: Laurie Strode, now the dean of a Northern California private school with an assumed name, must battle the Shape one last time, as the life of her own son hangs in the balance.

name: L.A. Story
description: With the help of a talking freeway billboard, a wacky weatherman tries to win the heart of an English newspaper reporter, who is struggling to make sense of the strange world of early 1990s Los Angeles.

name: Jerk, The
description: A simpleminded, sheltered country boy suddenly decides to leave his family home to experience life in the big city, where his naivete is both his best friend and his worst enemy.

name: Dead Men Don't Wear Plaid
description: Film noir parody with a detective uncovering a sinister plot. Characters from real noirs appear as scenes from various films are intercut.

name: Man with Two Brains, The
description: A brain surgeon marries a femme fatale, causing his life to turn upside down. Things go more awry when he falls in love with a talking brain.

name: Grand Canyon
description: The fates of several people are randomly intertwining. Their sympathy of each other faces multiple differences in their lifestyles.

name: Outsiders, The
description: The rivalry between two gangs, the poor Greasers and the rich Socs, only heats up when one gang member kills a member of the other.

name: Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom
description: In 1935, Indiana Jones is tasked by Indian villagers with reclaiming a rock stolen from them by a secret cult beneath the catacombs of an ancient palace.

name: Lord of the Rings, The
description: The Fellowship of the Ring embark on a journey to destroy the One Ring and end Sauron's reign over Middle-earth.
In a totalitarian future society, a man, whose daily work is re-writing history, tries to rebel by falling in love.

name: Dead Zone, The
description: A man awakens from a coma to discover he has a psychic ability.

name: Maximum Overdrive
description: A group of people try to survive when machines start to come alive and become homicidal.

name: Needful Things
description: A mysterious new shop opens in a small town which always seems to stock the deepest desires of each shopper, with a price far heavier than expected.

name: Cujo
description: Cujo, a friendly St. Bernard, contracts rabies and conducts a reign of terror on a small American town.

name: Children of the Corn
description: A young couple is trapped in a remote town where a dangerous religious cult of children believes that everyone over age 18 must be killed.

name: All Dogs Go to Heaven
description: A canine angel, Charlie, sneaks back to earth from heaven but ends up befriending an orphan girl who can speak to animals. In the process, Charlie learns that friendship is the most heavenly gift of all.

name: Addams Family, The
description: Con artists plan to fleece an eccentric family using an accomplice who claims to be their long-lost uncle.

name: Ever After: A Cinderella Story
description: The Brothers Grimm arrive at the home of a wealthy Grande Dame who speaks of the many legends surrounding the fable of the cinder girl before telling the 'true' story of her ancestor.

name: Snake Eyes
description: A shady police detective finds himself in the middle of a murder conspiracy at an important boxing match in an Atlantic City casino.

name: Atlantic City
description: In a corrupt city, a small-time gangster and the estranged wife of a pot dealer find themselves thrown together in an escapade of love, money, drugs and danger.

name: Autumn Sonata
description: A devoted wife is visited by her mother, a successful concert pianist who had little time for her when she was young.

name: Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?
description: A bitter, aging couple, with the help of alcohol, use their young houseguests to fuel anguish and emotional pain towards each other over the course of a distressing night.

name: Adventures in Babysitting
description: A babysitter must battle her way through the big city after being stranded there with the kids she's looking after.

name: Weird Science
description: Two high-school nerds use a computer program to literally create the perfect woman, who promptly turns their lives upside-down.

name: Doctor Dolittle
description: After the animal communicating veterinarian goes too far for his clientele, he and his friends escape their hometown to the sea in search of the Great Pink Sea Snail.

name: Nutty Professor, The
description: A timid, nearsighted chemistry teacher discovers a magical potion that can transform him into a suave and handsome Romeo. The Jekyll and Hyde game works well enough until the concoction starts to wear off at the most embarrassing ...

name: Charlotte's Web
description: Wilbur is a farm pig who's terrified that he'll end up on the dinner table. His friend Charlotte, a charming spider, comes to his rescue. She weaves words into her web, convincing the farmer that Wilbur is too special a pig to kill.

name: Watership Down
description: Hoping to escape destruction by human developers and save their community, a colony of rabbits, led by Hazel and Fiver, seek out a safe place to set up a new warren.

name: Secret of NIMH, The
description: To save her ill son, a field mouse must seek the aid of a colony of rats, with whom she has a deeper link than she suspected.

name: Dark Crystal, The
description: On another planet in the distant past, a Gelfling embarks on a quest to find the missing shard of a magical crystal, and to restore order to his world.

name: American Tail, An
description: While emigrating to the United States, a young Russian mouse gets separated from his family and must relocate them while trying to survive in a new country.

name: American Tail: Fievel Goes West, An
description: Fievel's family decides to move out to the West, unaware that they are falling into a trap perpetrated by a smooth-talking cat.

name: Legend
description: A young man must stop the Lord of Darkness from destroying daylight and marrying the woman he loves.

name: Sixteen Candles
description: A girl's 'sweet' sixteenth birthday is anything but special: her family forgets about it, and she suffers from every embarrassment possible.

name: Pretty in Pink
description: A poor girl must choose between the affections of dating her childhood sweetheart or a rich but sensitive playboy.

name: St. Elmo's Fire
description: A group of friends, just out of college, struggle with adulthood.

name: Clan of the Cave Bear, The
description: A young Cro-Magnon woman is raised by Neanderthals.

name: House
description: A troubled writer moves into a haunted house after inheriting it from his aunt.

name: House II: The Second Story
description: The new owner of a sinister house gets involved with reanimated corpses and demons searching for an ancient Aztec skull with magic powers.

name: Gods Must Be Crazy, The
description: A comic allegory about a traveling Bushman who encounters modern civilization and its stranger aspects, including a clumsy scientist and a band of revolutionaries.

name: Gods Must Be Crazy II, The
description: Six people meet in the Kalahari desert: a female NYC lawyer flying with a local zoologist/pilot in a mini-plane, a Cuban and an African soldier taking each other POW, a Boer elephant poacher, and a Bushman looking for his two chil...

name: Air Bud: Golden Receiver
description: Story of a golden retriever who can play football.

name: Avengers, The
description: Two British Agents team up to stop Sir August de Wynter from destroying the world with a weather-changing machine.

name: How Stella Got Her Groove Back
description: Stella is a highly successful, forty-something San Francisco stock broker who is persuaded by her colorful New York girlfriend Delilah to take a well deserved, first-class vacation to Jamaica.

name: Slums of Beverly Hills, The
description: In 1976, a lower-middle-class teenager struggles to cope living with her neurotic family of nomads on the outskirts of Beverly Hills.

name: Best Man, The
description: Incredibly, the bride at the altar falls in love with the best man on first sight, and even though he makes efforts to avoid her infatuation with him, she is determined to annul her marriage and marry the best man. And although sh...

name: Henry: Portrait of a Serial Killer
description: Arriving in Chicago, Henry moves in with ex-con acquaintance Otis and starts schooling him in the ways of the serial killer.

name: Rosemary's Baby
description: A young couple trying for a baby moves into an aging, ornate apartment building on Central Park West, where they find themselves surrounded by peculiar neighbors.

name: NeverEnding Story, The
description: A troubled boy dives into a wondrous fantasy world through the pages of a mysterious book.

name: NeverEnding Story II: The Next Chapter, The
description: A young boy with a distant father enters a world of make-believe and magic through a portal within an antique book.

name: Attack of the Killer Tomatoes!
description: A group of scientists band together to save the world from mutated killer tomatoes.

name: Surf Nazis Must Die
description: When the son of a gun-wielding woman is murdered by neo-Nazi surf punks in the post-apocalyptic future, his Mama hunts them down for some bloodthirsty revenge.

name: Your Friends and Neighbors
description: Unhappy couples fall apart and hop into other beds with other people.

name: Return to Paradise
description: Two friends must choose whether to help a third friend who was arrested in Malaysia for drug possession.

name: Blade
description: A half-vampire, half-mortal man becomes a protector of the mortal race, while slaying evil vampires.

name: Dead Man on Campus
description: Two college roommates go out and party, resulting in bad grades. They learn of the clause that says, 'If your roommate dies, you get an A,' and decide to find someone who is on the verge, so to speak, to move in with them.

name: Wrongfully Accused
description: Ryan Harrison is framed for murder and must prove himself innocent by finding a mysterious one-eyed, one-armed, one-legged man after escaping from a bus accident on the way to jail.

name: Next Stop Wonderland
description: An unlucky in love nurse finds her life taking a detour when her mother places a personals ad in the paper, while on the other side of Boston, a plumber is trying to change careers.

name: Strike!
description: In the 1960s, a group of friends at an all girls school learn that their school is going to be combined with a nearby all boys school. They concoct a plan to save their school while dealing with everyday problems along the way.

name: Beetlejuice
description: The spirits of a deceased couple are harassed by an unbearable family that has moved into their home, and hire a malicious spirit to drive them out.

name: Déjà Vu
description: L.A. shop owner Dana and Englishman Sean meet and fall in love at first sight, but Sean is married and Dana is to marry her business partner Alex.

name: Rope
description: Two men attempt to prove they committed the perfect crime by hosting a dinner party after strangling their former classmate to death.

name: Family Plot
description: A phony psychic/con artist and her taxi driver/actor boyfriend encounter a pair of serial kidnappers while trailing a missing heir in California.

name: Frenzy
description: A serial murderer is strangling women with a necktie. The London police have a suspect, but he is the wrong man.

name: Topaz
description: A French Intelligence Agent becomes embroiled in the Cold War politics first with uncovering the events leading up to the 1962 Cuban Missile Crisis, and then back to France to break up an international Russian spy ring.

name: Torn Curtain
description: An American scientist publicly defects to East Germany as part of a cloak and dagger mission to find the solution for a formula resin before planning an escape back to the West.

name: Marnie
description: Mark marries Marnie although she is a habitual thief and has serious psychological problems, and tries to help her confront and resolve them.

name: Wrong Man, The
description: In 1953, an innocent man named Christopher Emanuel 'Manny' Balestrero is arrested after being mistaken for an armed robber.

name: Man Who Knew Too Much, The
description: An American doctor and his wife, a former singing star, witness a murder while vacationing in Morocco, and are drawn into a twisting plot of international intrigue when their young son is kidnapped.

name: Trouble with Harry, The
description: Harry's dead and, while no one really minds, everyone feels responsible. After Harry's body is found in the woods, several locals must determine not only how and why he was killed but what to do with the body.

name: I Confess
description: A priest, who comes under suspicion for murder, cannot clear his name without breaking the seal of the confessional.

name: Strangers on a Train
description: A psychopath forces a tennis star to comply with his theory that two strangers can get away with murder.

name: Stage Fright
description: A struggling actress tries to help a friend prove his innocence after he's accused of murdering the husband of a high-society entertainer.
The famous 1970s New York City nightclub seen and told through the eyes of a young employee.

name: Why Do Fools Fall In Love?
description: Three women each claim to be the widow of 1950s doo-wop singer Frankie Lymon, claiming legal rights to his estate.

name: Willow

name: Untouchables, The

name: Dirty Work

name: Paradine Case, The

name: Ring, The

description: To stall a witch plotting to eat him, a boy reads her horror tales dealing with a collegian's resurrection of a mummy, a murderous cat, and an artist's pact with a gargoyle.

name: Hands on a Hard Body
description: Twenty-four contestants compete in an endurance/sleep deprivation contest in order to win a brand new Nissan Hardbody truck. The last person to remain standing with his or her hand on the truck wins. An absurd marketing gimmick at...

name: Celebration, The

description: Thirty years after the original monster's rampage, a new Godzilla emerges and attacks Japan.

name: King Kong vs. Godzilla
description: A UN reporter broadcasts a report on the appearance of a prehistoric monster that emerges from hibernation while a pharmaceutical company seeks publicity with a monster of their own. (US Version)

name: King Kong

name: King Kong
description: A petroleum exploration expedition comes to an isolated island and encounters a colossal giant gorilla.

name: King Kong Lives
description: Kong falls from the twin towers and he appears to be alive. However, his heart is failing, so it's replaced with an artificial one. All is well until he senses that there's a female Kong somewhere out there and escapes wreaking ha...

description: After a divorced New York mother hires a nice old man to play Santa Claus at Macy's, she is startled by his claim to be the genuine article. When his sanity is questioned, a lawyer defends him in court by arguing that he's not mis...

name: Extremities

name: Faculty, The

name: Mighty Joe Young
description: A legendary fifteen-foot tall mountain gorilla named Joe is taken to an animal sanctuary in California by zoologist Gregg O'Hara (Bill Paxton) and Jill Young (Charlize Theron), with whom he grew up. Poacher Strasser (Rade Serbedzi...

name: Mighty Joe Young

name: Patch Adams

description: A radical American journalist becomes involved with the Communist revolution in Russia, and hopes to bring its spirit and idealism to the United States.

name: Return with Honor
description: The story of U.S. fighter pilots shot down over North Vietnam who became POWs for up to 8 and a half years.

name: Time of the Gypsies
description: In this luminous tale set in the area around Sarajevo and in Italy, Perhan, an engaging young Romany (gypsy) with telekinetic powers, is seduced by the quick-cash world of petty crime, which threatens to destroy him and those he l...

name: Days of Heaven
description: A hot-tempered farm laborer convinces the woman he loves to marry their rich but dying boss so that they can have a claim to his fortune.

name: Lady Eve, The
description: A trio of classy card sharks targets a socially awkward brewery heir, until one of them falls in love with him.

name: Sullivan's Travels
description: Hollywood director John L. Sullivan sets out to experience life as a homeless person in order to gain relevant life experience for his next movie.

name: Palm Beach Story, The
description: A New York inventor needs cash to develop his big idea, so his adoring wife decides to raise it by divorcing him and marrying an eccentric Florida millionaire with a capricious high-society sister.

name: Niagara
description: As two couples are visiting Niagara Falls, tensions between one wife and her husband reach the level of murder.

name: Gilda
description: A small-time gambler hired to work in a Buenos Aires casino discovers his employer's new wife is his former lover.

name: South Pacific
description: On a South Pacific island during World War II, love blooms between a young nurse and a secretive Frenchman who's being courted for a dangerous military mission.

name: Flashdance
description: A Pittsburgh woman with two jobs as a welder and an exotic dancer wants to get into ballet school.

name: Indochine
description: Eliane adopts Camille, whose Vietnamese parents were friends. In 1930, a French navy officer is interested in Eliane (owns 60km2 plantation) and later in Camille. There's an uprising in Vietnam against French colonial power.

name: Dirty Dozen, The
description: During World War II, a rebellious U.S. Army Major is assigned a dozen convicted murderers to train and lead them into a mass assassination mission of German officers.

name: Help!
description: Sir Ringo Starr finds himself the human sacrifice target of a cult, and his fellow members of The Beatles must try to protect him from it.

name: Goldfinger
description: While investigating a gold magnate's smuggling, James Bond uncovers a plot to contaminate the Fort Knox gold reserve.

name: From Russia with Love
description: James Bond willingly falls into an assassination plot involving a naive Russian beauty in order to retrieve a Soviet encryption device that was stolen by S.P.E.C.T.R.E.

name: Dr. No
description: A resourceful British government agent seeks answers in a case involving the disappearance of a colleague and the disruption of the American space program.

name: Blue Lagoon, The
description: In the Victorian period, two children are shipwrecked on a tropical island in the South Pacific. With no adults to guide them, the two make a simple life together, unaware that sexual maturity will eventually intervene.

name: Fistful of Dollars, A
description: A wandering gunfighter plays two rival families against each other in a town torn apart by greed, pride, and revenge.

name: Sydney
description: Professional gambler Sydney teaches John the tricks of the trade. John does well until he falls for cocktail waitress Clementine.

name: Home Alone 2: Lost in New York
description: One year after Kevin McCallister was left home alone and had to defeat a pair of bumbling burglars, he accidentally finds himself stranded in New York City - and the same criminals are not far behind.

name: Someone to Watch Over Me
description: A married New York cop falls for the socialite murder witness he's been assigned to protect.

name: Fight Club
description: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soap maker form an underground fight club that evolves into much more.

name: Story of Us, The
description: Ben and Katie Jordan are a married couple who go through hard times in fifteen years of marriage.

name: Fever Pitch
description: A sports fan's romantic courtship clashes with his obsession with his favorite football team.

name: Julien Donkey-Boy
description: A portrait of the effects of schizophrenia on family life is the central focus.

name: Omega Code, The
description: A rabbi in Jerusalem develops software that can unlock prophecies in the Torah. He's murdered and the software stolen. A powerful man uses it to gain world domination.

name: Straight Story, The
description: An old man makes a long journey by lawnmower to mend his relationship with an ill brother.

name: Bad Seed, The
description: Rhoda Penmark seems like your average, sweet eight-year-old girl. When her rival at school dies in mysterious circumstances at the school picnic her mother starts to suspect that Rhoda was responsible.

name: Time Bandits
description: A young boy accidentally joins a band of time travelling dwarves, as they jump from era to era looking for treasure to steal.

name: Man and a Woman, A
description: A widow and a widower find their relationship developing into love, but their past tragedies prove hard to overcome, causing them to proceed with utmost delicacy.

name: Fitzcarraldo
description: The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.

name: All That Jazz
description: Director/choreographer Bob Fosse tells his own life story as he details the sordid career of Joe Gideon, a womanizing, drug-using dancer.

name: Red Sorghum
description: When a leprous winery owner in 1930s China dies a few days after his arranged marriage, his young widow is forced to run the winery to make a living while contending with bandits, her drunkard lover, and the invading Japanese army.

name: Crimes and Misdemeanors
description: An ophthalmologist's mistress threatens to reveal their affair to his wife while a married documentary filmmaker is infatuated with another woman.

name: Bats
description: Genetically mutated bats escape and it's up to a bat expert and the local sheriff to stop them.

name: Best Man, The
description: Just before his best friend's wedding, the life of a Chicago writer becomes crazy when his best friend guesses that his new book's story is based on his bride's fervent past.

name: Bringing Out the Dead
description: Haunted by the patients he failed to save, a monumentally burned-out Manhattan ambulance paramedic fights to maintain his sanity over three increasingly turbulent nights.

name: Crazy in Alabama
description: An abused wife heads to California to become a movie star while her nephew back in Alabama has to deal with a racially-motivated murder involving a corrupt sheriff.

name: Three to Tango
description: A rich businessman's assumption that his new colleague is gay leads him to ask the man to keep an eye on his mistress. However, the man is not gay, and begins to fall for the woman himself.

name: Body Shots
description: A tale of the mysterious, but necessary, mating ritual between men and women of today and everything they think about sex but are afraid to say.

name: Guardian, The
description: A young couple with a newborn baby don't realize that the nanny they hired is a magical nymph who sacrifices infants to an evil tree.

name: Ipcress File, The
description: In London, a wisecracking spy investigates the kidnapping and brainwashing of British scientists while dealing with the constraints of his agency's bureaucracy.

name: On Any Sunday
description: Documentary on motorcycle racing featuring stars of the sport, including film star Steve McQueen, a racer in his own right.

name: RoboCop
description: In a dystopic and crime-ridden Detroit, a terminally wounded cop returns to the force as a powerful cyborg haunted by submerged memories.

name: RoboCop 2
description: RoboCop returns to protect the citizens of old Detroit but faces a deadly challenge when a rogue OCP member secretly creates a new, evil RoboCop 2.

name: Who Framed Roger Rabbit?
description: A toon-hating detective is a cartoon rabbit's only hope to prove his innocence when he is accused of murder.

name: Melvin and Howard
description: The story of hard-luck Melvin E. Dummar, who claimed to have received a will naming him an heir to the fortune of Howard Hughes.

name: For Your Eyes Only
description: James Bond is assigned to find a missing British vessel, equipped with a weapons encryption device and prevent it from falling into enemy hands.

name: Licence to Kill
description: A vengeful James Bond goes rogue to infiltrate and take down the organization of a drug lord who has murdered his friend's new wife and left him near death.

name: Live and Let Die
description: James Bond is sent to stop a diabolically brilliant heroin magnate armed with a complex organisation and a reliable psychic tarot card reader.

name: Rawhead Rex
description: An ancient creature called Rawhead is awakened from its slumber near an Irish village and goes on a rampage killing anyone in sight.

name: Thunderball
description: James Bond heads to the Bahamas to recover two nuclear warheads stolen by S.P.E.C.T.R.E. Agent Emilio Largo in an international extortion scheme.

name: House on Haunted Hill
description: An amusement park mogul offers a group of diverse people $1,000,000 to spend the night in a haunted house with a horrifying past.

name: Music of the Heart
description: Story of a schoolteacher's struggle to teach violin to inner-city Harlem kids.

name: Being John Malkovich
description: A puppeteer discovers a portal that leads literally into the head of movie star John Malkovich.

name: Princess Mononoke
description: On a journey to find the cure for a Tatarigami's curse, Ashitaka finds himself in the middle of a war between the forest gods and Tatara, a mining colony. In this quest he also meets San, the Mononoke Hime.

name: My Best Fiend
description: In the 1950s, an adolescent Werner Herzog was transfixed by a film performance of the young Klaus Kinski. Years later, they would share an apartment where, in an unabated, forty-eight-hour fit of rage, Kinski completely destroyed ...

name: Train of Life
description: In 1941, the inhabitants of a small Jewish village in Central Europe organize a fake deportation train so that they can escape the Nazis and flee to Palestine.

name: Bachelor, The
description: A commitment-phobic man goes in search of a bride, including his fed-up girlfriend, to inherit his grandfather's one hundred million dollar inheritance.

name: Bone Collector, The
description: A quadriplegic ex-homicide detective and his partner try to track down a serial killer who is terrorizing New York City.

name: Insider, The
description: A research chemist comes under personal and professional attack when he decides to appear in a 60 Minutes exposé on Big Tobacco.

name: American Movie
description: Documentary about an aspiring filmmaker's attempts to finance his dream project by finally completing the low-budget horror film he abandoned years before.

name: Last Night
description: A group of very different individuals with different ideas of how to face the end come together as the world is expected to end in six hours at the turn of the century.

name: Rosetta
description: Young and impulsive Rosetta lives with her alcoholic mother and, moved by despair, she will do anything to maintain a job.

name: They Shoot Horses, Don't They?
description: The lives of a disparate group of contestants intertwine in an inhumanely grueling dance marathon.

name: Bride of Re-Animator
description: Doctors Herbert West and Dan Cain discover the secret to creating human life and proceed to create a perfect woman from dead tissue.

name: Bustin' Loose
description: Failed parolee Joe Braxton has one last shot at redemption: by driving school kids to Philadelphia.

name: Coma
description: When a young female doctor notices an unnatural amount of comas occurring in her hospital she uncovers a horrible conspiracy.

name: Creepshow
description: Five grisly tales from a kid's comic book about a murdered father rising from his grave, a bizarre meteor, a vengeful husband, a mysterious crate's occupant, and a plague of cockroaches.

name: Creepshow 2
description: Three macabre tales from the latest issue of a boy's favorite comic book, dealing with a vengeful wooden Native American, a monstrous blob in a lake, and an undying hitchhiker.

name: Re-Animator
description: After an odd new medical student arrives on campus, a dedicated local and his girlfriend become involved in bizarre experiments centering around the re-animation of dead tissue.

name: Drugstore Cowboy
description: A pharmacy-robbing dope fiend and his crew pop pills and evade the law.

name: Falling Down
description: An ordinary man frustrated with the various flaws he sees in society begins to psychotically and violently lash out against them.

name: Funhouse, The
description: Four teenagers visit a local carnival for a night of innocent amusement, but soon discover that nothing there is innocent or amusing.

name: General, The
description: After being rejected by the Confederate military, not realizing it was due to his crucial civilian role, an engineer must single-handedly recapture his beloved locomotive after it is seized by Union spies and return it through ene...

name: Piranha
description: When flesh-eating piranhas are accidentally released into a summer resort's rivers, the guests become their next meal.

name: Taming of the Shrew, The
description: Brutish, fortune-hunting scoundrel Petruchio tames his wealthy, shrewish wife, Katharina.

name: Nighthawks
description: When one of Europe's most lethal terrorists shows up in New York, an elite undercover cop is assigned to take him down by any means necessary.

name: Yojimbo
description: A crafty ronin comes to a town divided by two criminal gangs and decides to play them against each other to free the town.

name: Repossessed
description: Parody of The Exorcist (1973), with Linda Blair once again possessed by Satan, and Leslie Nielsen as the exorcist.

name: Omega Man, The
description: Biological war has decimated life on Earth. Los Angeles is a windswept ghost town where Robert Neville tools his convertible through sunlit streets foraging for supplies.

name: Spaceballs
description: A star-pilot for hire and his trusty sidekick must come to the rescue of a princess and save Planet Druidia from the clutches of the evil Spaceballs.

name: Robin Hood
description: The story of the legendary British outlaw portrayed with the characters as anthropomorphic animals.

name: Mister Roberts
description: In the waning days of World War II, the cargo officer of a Navy supply ship chafes at its role far from the action in the Pacific's backwater areas, his frustration rising when its captain denies the crew liberty over petty irrita...

name: Quest for Fire
description: This story takes place in prehistoric time when three tribesmen search for a new fire source.

name: Little Big Man
description: Jack Crabb, looking back from extreme old age, tells of his life being raised by Native Americans and fighting with General Custer.

name: Face in the Crowd, A
description: A female radio reporter turns a folk-singing drifter into a powerful media star.

name: Trading Places
description: A snobbish investor and a wily street con artist find their positions reversed as part of a bet by two callous millionaires.

name: Meatballs
description: Wacky hijinks of counselors and campers at a less-than-average summer camp.

name: Meatballs Part II
description: Second in the series of Meatball movies. A group of kids attempt to save a summer camp that's a financial failure.

name: Meatballs III
description: The ghost of a dead porn star comes to Earth to help a nerd with his sex life.

name: Meatballs 4
description: Ricky is the hottest water-ski instructor around and he has just been rehired by his former employer/camp to whip up attendance. But the camp is in serious financial trouble and the owner of a rival, more popular, camp wants to bu...

name: Dead Again
description: A woman who has lost her memory is taken in by a Los Angeles orphanage, and a private eye is enlisted to track down her identity, but he soon finds that he might have a past life connection to her that endangers their lives.

name: Peter's Friends
description: Six former college friends, with two new friends, gather for a New Year's Eve weekend reunion at a large English countryside manor after ten years to reminisce about the good times now long gone.

name: Incredibly True Adventure of Two Girls in Love, The
description: An adventurous love story between two young women of different social and economic backgrounds who find themselves going through all the typical struggles of a new romance.

name: Under the Rainbow
description: A visiting dignitary, a CIA agent, a Nazi spy, Japanese tourists, an assassin and a group of 'midget' actors from The Wizard of Oz (1939) all check into an elite Los Angeles hotel called Under the Rainbow.

name: Anywhere But Here
description: A mother and daughter search for success in Beverly Hills.

name: Dogma
description: An abortion clinic worker with a special heritage is called upon to save the existence of humanity from being negated by two renegade angels trying to exploit a loop-hole and reenter Heaven.

name: Messenger: The Story of Joan of Arc, The
description: A young girl receives a vision that drives her to rid France of its oppressors.

name: Pokémon: The First Movie
description: Scientists genetically create a new Pokémon, Mewtwo, but the results are horrific and disastrous.

name: Felicia's Journey
description: A young woman leaves Ireland to find her boyfriend in England, and while there is helped by a man hiding unsettling secrets.

name: Oxygen
description: Two guys kidnap the wife of a rich man and bury her in a box with 24 hours of oxygen. Tough NYPD Detective Maddy and others get the case. Will they get to her in time?

name: Where's Marlowe?
description: After making a 3-hour fiasco about New York City's water supply, a two-man film crew decides to take it up a notch by documenting life in the private investigator offices of 'Boone and Murphy'.

name: Commitments, The
description: Jimmy Rabbitte, an unemployed Dublin boy, decides to put together a soul band made up entirely of the Irish working class.

name: Holiday Inn
description: At an inn which is open only on holidays, a crooner and a hoofer vie for the affections of a beautiful up-and-coming performer.

name: Longest Day, The
description: The events of D-Day, told on a grand scale from both the Allied and German points of view.

name: Poison Ivy
description: A seductive teen befriends an introverted high school student and schemes her way into the lives of her wealthy family.

name: Poison Ivy: New Seduction
description: A sinister seductress vows to destroy a suburban family.

name: Tora! Tora! Tora!
description: The story of the 1941 Japanese air raid on Pearl Harbor, and the series of preceding American blunders that aggravated its effectiveness.

name: Women on the Verge of a Nervous Breakdown
description: A television actress encounters a variety of eccentric characters after embarking on a journey to discover why her lover abruptly left her.

name: Verdict, The
description: An outcast, alcoholic Boston lawyer sees the chance to salvage his career and self-respect by taking a medical malpractice case to trial rather than settling.

name: Adventures of Buckaroo Banzai Across the 8th Dimension, The
description: Adventurer, brain surgeon, rock musician Buckaroo Banzai and his crime-fighting team, the Hong Kong Cavaliers, must stop evil alien invaders from the eighth dimension who are planning to conquer Earth.

name: Stand and Deliver
description: The story of Jaime Escalante, a high school teacher who successfully inspired his dropout-prone students to learn calculus.

name: Moonstruck
description: Loretta Castorini, a bookkeeper from Brooklyn, New York, finds herself in a difficult situation when she falls for the brother of the man she has agreed to marry.

name: Sandpiper, The
description: A free-spirited single mother forms a connection with the married headmaster of an Episcopalian boarding school in Monterey, California.

name: Jeremiah Johnson
description: A mountain man who wishes to live the life of a hermit becomes the unwilling object of a long vendetta by the Crow tribe and proves to be a match for their warriors in single combat on the early frontier.

name: Repulsion
description: A sex-repulsed woman who disapproves of her sister's boyfriend sinks into depression and has horrific visions of rape and violence.

name: Irma la Douce
description: When a policeman falls in love with a prostitute, he doesn't want her seeing other men and creates an alter ego who's to be her only customer.

name: 42 Up
description: Director Michael Apted revisits the same group of British-born adults after a seven-year wait. The subjects are interviewed as to the changes that have occurred in their lives during the last seven years.

name: Liberty Heights
description: Baltimore, Fall 1954: Schools implement the new integration law. Ben finds the 'colored' girl in his class cute - upsetting his Jewish mom and granny. Ben talks to her while his brother looks for his WASP dream girl.

name: Mansfield Park
description: Fanny, born into a poor family, is sent away to live with wealthy uncle Sir Thomas, his wife and their four children, where she'll be brought up for a proper introduction to society.

name: Sleepy Hollow
description: Ichabod Crane is sent to Sleepy Hollow to investigate the decapitations of three people; the culprit is legendary apparition The Headless Horseman.

name: World Is Not Enough, The
description: James Bond uncovers a nuclear plot while protecting an oil heiress from her former kidnapper, an international terrorist who can't feel pain.

name: All About My Mother
description: Pedro Almodovar's Oscar-winning comedy (Best Foreign Film, 1999) about a bereaved mother, and overwrought actress, her jealous lover and a pregnant nun.

name: Babes in Toyland
description: Opposing the evil Barnaby, Ollie Dee and Stanley Dum try and fail to pay-off Mother Peep's mortgage and mislead his attempts to marry Little Bo. Enraged, Barnaby's Bogeymen are set on Toyland.

name: Scrooged
description: A selfish, cynical television executive is haunted by three spirits bearing lessons on Christmas Eve.

name: Harvey
description: Due to his insistence that he has an invisible six foot-tall rabbit for a best friend, a whimsical middle-aged man is thought by his family to be insane - but he may be wiser than anyone knows.

name: Bicycle Thieves
description: In post-war Italy, a working-class man's bicycle is stolen, endangering his efforts to find work. He and his son set out to find it.

name: Matewan
description: A labor union organizer comes to an embattled mining community brutally and violently dominated and harassed by the mining company.

name: Kagemusha
description: A petty thief with an utter resemblance to a samurai warlord is hired as the lord's double. When the warlord later dies the thief is forced to take up arms in his place.

name: McCabe & Mrs. Miller
description: A gambler and a prostitute become business partners in a remote Old West mining town, and their enterprise thrives until a large corporation arrives on the scene.

name: Maurice
description: Two English school chums find themselves falling in love at Cambridge. To regain his place in society, Clive gives up Maurice and marries. While staying with Clive and his wife, Maurice discovers romance in the arms of the gamekee...

name: Grapes of Wrath, The
description: An Oklahoma family, driven off their farm by the poverty and hopelessness of the Dust Bowl, joins the westward migration to California, suffering the misfortunes of the homeless in the Great Depression.

name: My Man Godfrey
description: The spoiled daughter of a rich American family hires as butler an Austrian vagrant she finds on a pier, without knowing that he illegally jumped ship.

name: Shop Around the Corner, The
description: Two employees at a gift shop can barely stand each other, without realizing that they are falling in love through the post as each other's anonymous pen pal.

name: Natural, The
description: A middle-aged unknown comes seemingly out of nowhere to become a legendary baseball player with almost supernatural talent.

name: Shampoo
description: On Election Day, 1968, a hairdresser and ladies' man is too busy cutting hair and dealing with his various girlfriends and his mistress, whose husband he meets and finds out is having an affair with his ex-girlfriend.

name: River Runs Through It, A
description: Two sons of a stern minister - one reserved, one rebellious - grow up in rural 1920s Montana while devoted to fly fishing.

name: Fatal Attraction
description: A married man's one-night stand comes back to haunt him when that lover begins to stalk him and his family.

name: Jagged Edge
description: A wealthy woman is murdered in her beach house. The husband is allegedly knocked out first. He inherits all. He has a female ex criminal prosecutor represent him in court.

name: Stanley & Iris
description: A struggling widow falls in love with an illiterate short-order cook whom she teaches to read and write in her kitchen each night.

name: Midnight Run
description: A bounty hunter pursues a former Mafia accountant who is also being chased by a rival bounty hunter, the F.B.I., and his old mob boss after jumping bail.

name: Awakenings
description: The victims of an encephalitis epidemic many years ago have been catatonic ever since, but now a new drug offers the prospect of reviving them.

name: Come See the Paradise
description: The passionate romance between an Irish-American man and a Japanese-American woman is threatened when the Pearl Harbor attacks happen and the woman is forced into a prison camp because of her ethnicity.

name: Backdraft
description: Two Chicago firefighter brothers, who don't get along, have to work together while a dangerous arsonist is on the loose.

name: Fisher King, The
description: A former radio DJ, suicidally despondent because of a terrible mistake he made, finds redemption in helping a deranged homeless man who was an unwitting victim of that mistake.

name: River, The
description: A farming family battles severe storms, a bank is threatening to repossess their farm, and there are other hard times in a battle to save and hold on to their farm.

name: Places in the Heart
description: In central Texas in the 1930s, a widow with two small children tries to save her small 40-acre farm with the help of a blind boarder and an itinerant black handyman.

name: 'night Mother
description: A mother and daughter spend a night together after the daughter reveals that she will kill herself by the end of it.

name: End of Days
description: At the end of the century, Satan visits New York in search of a bride. It's up to an ex-cop who now runs an elite security outfit to stop him.

name: Toy Story 2
description: When Woody is stolen by a toy collector, Buzz and his friends set out on a rescue mission to save Woody before he becomes a museum toy property with his roundup gang Jessie, Prospector, and Bullseye.

name: Flawless
description: An ultraconservative security guard suffers a debilitating stroke and is assigned to a rehabilitative program that includes singing lessons with the drag queen next door.

name: Ride with the Devil
description: During the American Civil War, two friends join the Bushwhackers, a militant group loyal to the Confederacy.

name: Distinguished Gentleman, The
description: A conman discovers during a 'job' that US Congress is where the money is. 'Name recognition' gets him elected. Will he develop a conscience?

name: End of the Affair, The
description: A desperate man tries to find out why his beloved left him years ago.

name: Holy Smoke
description: Ruth's been brainwashed by a guru in Delhi, India. Her parents in Sydney hire a specialist in reversing this. Ruth is tricked to return to Australia and is isolated in an outback cabin with the specialist. It gets messy.

name: Sweet and Lowdown
description: In the 1930s, jazz guitarist Emmet Ray idolizes Django Reinhardt, faces gangsters and falls in love with a mute woman.

name: Bonfire of the Vanities
description: After his mistress runs over a young teen, a Wall Street hotshot sees his life unravel in the spotlight and attracts the interest of a down-and-out reporter.

name: Daddy Long Legs
description: An orphan discovers that she has an anonymous benefactor who is willing to pay her college tuition, unaware he's the same man who has been romantically pursuing her.

name: Grand Illusion
description: During WWI, two French soldiers are captured and imprisoned in a German P.O.W. camp. Several escape attempts follow until they are eventually sent to a seemingly inescapable fortress.

name: Great Santini, The
description: As he approaches manhood, Ben Meechum struggles to win the approval of his demanding alpha male father, an aggressively competitive, but frustrated Marine pilot.

name: Stealing Home
description: Ex-baseball player Billy comes home to receive his childhood darling's ashes.

name: Two Jakes, The
description: The sequel to Chinatown (1974) finds J.J. 'Jake' Gittes investigating adultery and murder, and the money that comes from oil.

name: U2: Rattle and Hum
description: A documentary of the Irish rock group U2 on their Fall 1987 tour of North America.

name: Hell in the Pacific
description: During World War II, an American pilot and a marooned Japanese navy captain are deserted on a small uninhabited island in the Pacific Ocean. There, they must cease their hostility and cooperate if they want to survive, but will they?

name: Cradle Will Rock
description: A true story of politics and art in the 1930s U.S., focusing on a leftist musical drama and attempts to stop its production.

name: Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo
description: An average aquarium cleaner house-sits for a gigolo, only to be forced to become one himself.

name: Green Mile, The
description: A tale set on death row in a Southern jail, where gentle giant John possesses the mysterious power to heal people's ailments. When the lead guard, Paul, recognizes John's gift, he tries to help stave off the condemned man's execut...

name: Cider House Rules, The
description: A compassionate young man, raised in an orphanage and trained to be a doctor there, decides to leave to see the world.

name: War Zone, The
description: An alienated teenager, saddened that he has moved away from London, must find a way to deal with a dark family secret.

name: Last Picture Show, The
description: In 1951, a group of high schoolers come of age in a bleak, isolated, atrophied North Texas town that is slowly dying, both culturally and economically.

name: 7th Voyage of Sinbad, The
description: When a princess is shrunken by an evil wizard, Sinbad must undertake a quest to an island of monsters to cure her and prevent a war.

name: Anna and the King
description: The story of the romance between the King of Siam and widowed British schoolteacher, Anna Leonowens, during the 1860s.

name: Bicentennial Man
description: An android endeavors to become human as he gradually acquires emotions.

name: Stuart Little
description: The Little family adopt a charming young mouse named Stuart, but the family cat wants rid of him.

name: Emperor and the Assassin, The
description: In pre-unified China, the King of Qin sends his concubine to a rival kingdom to produce an assassin for a political plot, but as the king's cruelty mounts she finds her loyalty faltering.

name: Fantasia 2000
description: An update of the original film with new interpretations of great works of classical music.

name: Magnolia
description: An epic mosaic of interrelated characters in search of love, forgiveness and meaning in the San Fernando Valley.

name: Onegin
description: Russia, 1820s: Onegin inherits his uncle's country estate and moves there from St. Petersburg. He befriends his neighbor, Lensky, and meets Tatyana through him. She falls in love with Onegin but he just wants friendship.

name: Simpatico
description: After scams at horse races and making lots of money, 3 young people split. 20 years later, one of them, a drunk, creates chaos with photos from back then.

name: Topsy-Turvy
description: Set in the 1880s, the story of how, during a creative dry spell, the partnership of the legendary musical/theatrical writers Gilbert and Sullivan almost dissolves, before they turn it all around and write the Mikado.

name: Boiling Point
description: A pair of sociopath killers take on the police and the mob in order to make one last big score.

name: Carnal Knowledge
description: Chronicling the lifelong sexual development of two men who meet and become friends in college.

name: Easy Rider
description: Two bikers head from L.A. to New Orleans through the open country and desert lands, and along the way they meet a man who bridges a counter-culture gap of which they had been unaware.

name: The Falcon and the Snowman
description: The true story of a disillusioned military contractor employee and his drug pusher childhood friend who became walk-in spies for the Soviet Union.

description: N/A

name: Northanger Abbey

Inspired by a true story, a comedy centered on a 27-year-old guy who learns of his cancer diagnosis and his subsequent struggle to beat the disease.

name: Generation P

name: The Artist

name: In Time

name: Rollo and the Woods Sprite
description: Troll-like rolleys find a village of goblins of the forest and take it as their own. The oldest of the rolley tribe leaves the community as it has came the time of him to rest and the tribe to choose a new lead. One rolley named R...

name: Civil War, The

name: John Carter
